Text: There doesn't seem to be anyone here.

No. I've been observing foot traffic in the area for the
past three days, and there are no regular visitors.

Even without the haunting, everyone in the city knows
that this place is under the watch of the real estate
guildâ€”

I doubt anyone wants to go trespassing in a place
that already seems like it's mired in trouble.
...You really are thorough, aren't you.

Well, that's because I'm a gal who knows how to get
things done, just like you!
Oh, yes, of course...
She's complimenting you, Gamma.
No, Lady Alpha. This is base flattery.
Oh really?
Iota is quite skilled at buttering me up.

She always smooth-talks me when she wants something.
That's why she said it.
Aw, c'mon. You do like compliments, though, right?
...Yes, I suppose they aren't entirely displeasing.

But more importantly! Do you really intend to wear
that when we sneak in?
Uh, yeah?
Now hold onâ€”

Look, what we're doing is illegal, but it's also
pretty much the same as a private viewing of a new
home, see? In that case, wouldn't it be best to get a
feel for it in our normal clothes, too?

Well, yes, I suppose checking such things is
important... What do you think, Lady Alpha?

I don't see any problem. If the interior doesn't
prove ideal for regular use, it can provide insight
for judging the value of the property.

Now then, let's head inside. Gamma, Iota, you watch
our flank.
Yes, ma'am!
This...
What the...?
N-No way... They call this haunted?!
It's a little messy, but this isn't ruined at all!

There are Tuna King wrappers, half-empty bottles...
Basically a bunch of trashâ€”

No way can you call a place that sees this much use a
haunted house! Somebody, no, make that a royal
doofus, is using this as their hangout!

...This is a puzzle, isn't it. If someone is indeed
taking up residence this place, they certainly are
leaving it defenseless.

Just to reconfirm, Iota, you're certain there's
no one here?

Y-Yes, of course...! I haven't seen a soul for three
entire days!

Though waiting for our arrival seems to have
backfired...there's no reason to be upset, Iota.
...Thank you, Lady Alpha.

This could mean that someone is staying here
illegally at irregular intervals.

But this is all rather bold, or maybe thoughtless...
Dare I say that our unlawful tenant doesn't know what
sort of place this is?

...Iota. This haunting...what kind of phenomena are
we talking about? Just noises and shadows?

No...! There are actual eyewitness accounts of the
ghost!

In that case, this "unlawful tenant" as Gamma puts it,
may be no ordinary squatter.

...You mean to say someone with the ability to
control the spirits of the dead?!

That's one possibility, but it's only that.
A possibility.

Is this lack of any sort of defenses simple
carelessness? Or is it indicative of a certain sort
of daring?

Let's stay on our toes and continue the
investigation.
Yes, ma'am!
...There doesn't seem to be anyone here.

It doesn't appear that this dungeon saw any use at
all. This place must have been removed from any
strife even during its time as a manor house.
Looks more like it was used for storage... Hmm?
What is it, Iota? Did you find something?

Well, it's just this crate doesn't have any dust on
it, see.

No signs of magic or traps, either... What do you
think, Lady Alpha?
...Open it, but be careful.
Understoodâ€”
...Hmm?
Are these...bundles of documents?
...Whoa! Gammy, get a load of this!
Now what's gotten into youâ€”
...Oh my! This is incredible!
Did you find something?
It appears to be some kind of registry of names!
A registry of names?
Yes...!

Baron Babyman...Baron Kidman...Baron Youngman...
Baron Grownman...Count Oldmanâ€”wait, Count Oldman?!
You know him?

Do I know him? He's only the prime minister of the
Altena Empire! You should at least know the names of
the major political figures of our neighboring
nations!

A-Aw, c'mon... I mean, duh, I knew that, but just
thought I'd go with the flow and ask!

Count Oldman...point of note..."wears a toupee."
So that outlandishly thick head of hair really is fakeâ€”

What we may have here is a list of highly classified
information about the aristocracy of the Altena
Empire!

Gamma. Check the documents to see if there's anything
with markings of the Cult of Diablos.
On it!
...There!

I think it's safe to consider this a list of personal
information on aristocrats compiled by the Cult in
absolute secrecy!

As I suspected... What does it say about other
aristocrats?

Let's see... There are notes saying "bad drunk,"
"avid gambler," "disinherited unworthy eldest son,"
and "accidental death in own mithril mine was
concealed."

The personal information columns on the other pages
all generally contain something.

All useful clues to help the Cult exploit the
weaknesses of the aristocrat in question, I'm sure.

Why would they keep crazy documents full of super
secret stuff all bundled up in a place like this?

That's a good question... Why would a location with
nearly no defenses house vital intel of a sort not
often found elsewhere?

It'd make more sense if it dated back to the days of
Altena's independence, but this is about the empire
in its current state.

Normally we would never obtain information on the
Cult this easily, though!

Then let's confirm what's going on here using a more
direct method.
Direct...?
That is to say, we wait here for someone to comeâ€”
